### Instruction
Propose a repository-grounded design and include evidence code snippets and a reasoning trace.
Business context:Rule:Order status transition update / Stock lock/reservation rule / Stock release/unlock rule
Requirement:Design unified validation and auditing for the rule 'Order status transition update / Stock lock/reservation rule / Stock release/unlock rule': centralized checks, audit logs, consistent error semantics, and concrete components.

### Response
{
  "design": {
    "architecture_overview": "Based on the existing layered architecture (Controller/Service/Mapper), introduce minimal closed-loop components in the stock domain and reuse existing patterns.",
    "evidence_hints": [
      "Focus on entry methods:addCriterion, andIdIsNull, andIdIsNotNull",
      "Layers hinted:other",
      "Evidence files:mall-mbg/src/main/java/com/macro/mall/model/PmsProductAttributeExample.java, mall-mbg/src/main/java/com/macro/mall/model/UmsMemberMemberTagRelationExample.java",
      "Requirement type:rule-validation-audit"
    ],
    "strategy_set": [
      "Stock reserve TTL + timeout release job",
      "Idempotency key(requestId) + dedup table",
      "Optimistic lock/conditional update(concurrency-safe)"
    ],
    "strategy_ids": [
      "ttl_reserve",
      "idempotency_key",
      "optimistic_lock"
    ],
    "components": [
      "StockReserveService(new/extend): reserve/release/confirm entry points(idempotent)",
      "StockReserveMapper(new): persistence for reserve records",
      "StockReleaseJob(new): timeout release scanner job",
      "RuleValidatorRegistry(new): plug-in validators for rule 'business rule'",
      "ErrorSemanticCatalog(new): stable error codes and standardized semantics",
      "RuleAuditService(new): audit rule evaluation(inputs/outputs/errors)",
      "ReserveTTLPolicy(new): TTL policy and expiry handling",
      "IdempotencyService(new): validate idempotency key and dedup records",
      "VersionedUpdateHelper(new): conditional update and retry-on-conflict"
    ],
    "apis": [
      "POST /stock/reserve: reserve stock(returns reserveId/expireAt)",
      "POST /stock/release: release reservation(idempotent)",
      "POST /stock/confirm: confirm deduction(idempotent)",
      "POST /rule/validate: centralized validation(return standardized errors)"
    ],
    "data_model": [
      "stock_reserve(id,reserve_id,order_id,sku_id,qty,status,expire_at,created_at,updated_at)",
      "rule_audit(id,rule_id,biz_id,inputs,result,error_code,created_at)",
      "idempotency_record(id,key,biz_type,biz_id,status,created_at)"
    ],
    "sequence_flows": [
      "1)Centralized validation entry(carries requestId/traceId) selects the proper validator",
      "2)Run checks and output standardized error semantics(code/message/retryability)",
      "3)Persist rule_audit(inputs/result/errors) and return consistent failure responses",
      "4)Optionally trigger async handling via outbox/jobs(alerting/compensation/reconcile)"
    ],
    "risk_and_mitigation": [
      "Strategy:Stock reserve TTL + timeout release job.Key points:reserve records, expire_at, release job scanner",
      "Strategy:Idempotency key(requestId) + dedup table.Key points:dedup table, unique constraint, replay has no side effects",
      "Strategy:Optimistic lock/conditional update(concurrency-safe).Key points:version field, conditional update, retry-on-conflict policy"
    ],
    "repo_constraints": [
      "Follow the existing Controller/Service/Mapper layering.",
      "Prefer reusing existing order/stock service and mapper patterns.",
      "State changes and stock changes must be idempotent and auditable(traceable)."
    ]
  },
